<subSubSection id="FCD63830A5227D22DF4588D02B245ECE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E2AEAA2F85B6578A44477D5383E100CD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96DD56B9C488FED29D66D414959ED2C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="F9259778D23970ED798DDB30CCF5AEAC" authority="Bigot, 1882" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Romaleosyrphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Romaleosyrphus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E9D7A566A764D63B5450D132687C55FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Romaleosyrphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="D8D96D7C71A2C58AE2C68742CE44FAC6" authorityName="Moran &amp; Skevington" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Criorhina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Criorhina" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4FAC000A3B71B4D13BE03389278F749" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Criorhina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4CD8B887BF362A4973ACEA4B837DDD44" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphecomyia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecomyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7DDF702C25E3EAC3B90ED9C92C5048E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sphecomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters. Male eye contiguous for ca. 1/2 length of ocellar triangle. Oval shaped postpedical. Broad intersection of vein R1 with vein C. Proximal ventral half of vein C with setae. Abdominal pile appressed. Male genitalia with phallapodeme keeled and laterally sclerotized, not banana-shaped. It is further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="69D4FB30378257F94A903E35162D014A" authorityName="Shiraki" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Matsumyia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Matsumyia" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="565C1B77C5DC8B1477D2D45E9FA2E7A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Matsumyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a distal part of vein R4+5 beyond vein M1 longer than cross-vein h.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0DF269F36D6CCCBD771E8EB9C1E630A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="redescription">
<paragraph id="4E46A11B6980A405D37A6A3765AA1CC8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DCC75C94A2AD1A51FBD2108137C3FC73" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="3A15D20A6B3BAC53DBF4B6709A47D4E7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MALE.</emphasis>
Body length: 13.0-17.1 mm. Wing length: 8.0-12.1 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="73AE7DB2318648A7BF9D0CCD51DFDD5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="5A6F4FD35460C11BC98F65602CAACB53" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head.</emphasis>
Face black, produced downwards and completely pruinose, concave beneath antenna, tuberculate; gena broad, as broad or broader than long, bare, shiny, pilose posteriorly; anterior tentorial pit short, extending along ventral third of eye, pilose; frontal prominence distinct; frons broad and pruinose; vertex triangular, longer than broad and always pilose; ocellar triangle small; eye bare, contiguous for ca. 1/2 length of ocellar triangle; head oval in shape; length of antenna segments in a 3:3:2 ratio; postpedical oval, with bare arista dorsally placed.
</paragraph>
<caption id="836844759C41BB2C9AEA11C6F952A3DF" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.55862.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/619712" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="26F8821DA92A3208F27BF6B01E866AC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="50AD9BAA3E721AC2D6C7B90030FAD90E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DDA5865630DF3764BC37832F0CC95B96" authority="Bigot, 1882" authorityName="Moran" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Romaleosyrphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Romaleosyrphus bigoti" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigoti">
<emphasis id="8C62A72A4F3A1934F87C7F53A0534663" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Romaleosyrphus bigoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C2D80E60B77EDB8A25C54F49666F8BDE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="EB4B7BD7A61BF67BA22FC5C1F06A272F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="6E023356F977EB7D17B91D12BBA866E6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Ca. as long as broad, long pilose; postpronotum pilose; proepimeron pilose; anterior anepisternum bare, posterior anepisternum pilose; scutellum without apical sulcus and with ventral pile fringe; katepisternum bare anteriorly, discontinuously pilose posteriorly with broadly separated patches; anepimeron with anterior portion pilose, and dorsomedial and posterior portion bare; katepimeron bare; metathoracic pleuron bare; without hypopleural pile at the base of the posterior thoracic spiracle; meron bare; metathoracic spiracle ca. same size as postpedical; metasternum pilose; postmetacoxal bridge incomplete; plumula simple, elongate, short, not reaching calypteral margin; calypter brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="2C6D70329D3783EF7358EB6EF6E9081B" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.55862.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/619713" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="E277C18BC60D38DEC39E814588DB2C1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="8AE037EC47B9DC9F24D91FF599E6E95B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="99EF6764FC819854D9AA272CC7660485" authority="Bigot, 1882" authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Romaleosyrphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Romaleosyrphus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="99ED6A78C90D2FBA08918DA44BD87A7B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Romaleosyrphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distribution.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C52534E52480B3CCBA320B988ED46FE5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="0573B9DD029CB3C652A9600DD5810387" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="D35ABBAEEDA05D2E4FFB690119172E64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Coxae pilose anteriorly, bare posteriorly; hind trochanter sometimes tuberculate in male; metafemur swollen, curved, with large apicoventral ridge and without basiventral setose patch; metatibia transverse apically, rounded basiventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F7A243B27F1CB5C7D552F894A97842B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="B9A573F120F2C91064E900295AD31DA2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="073A38DC822E480B1B555C9A00797591" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wing</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Cell r1 open; stigmatic cross vein present; cross-vein r-m at outer 
<normalizedToken id="018EC4D6A25BA012688D0D7D3282C0C0" originalValue="¼">1/4</normalizedToken>
of cell dm; broad intersection of vein R1 with vein C (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F4DB8348174AC27D751427BB2C3EBB44" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Intersection of vein R 1 with vein C (white), distance between apices of veins R 1 and R 2 + 3 and apices of veins R 2 + 3 and R 4 + 5 (blue), distal vein R 4 + 5 (pink) and setosity of proximal ventral half of vein C (red). A Romaleosyrphus bigoti sp. nov. B Sphecomyia weismani (Moran) C Criorhina bubulcus (Walker)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.55862.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/619714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3</figureCitation>
); vein R4+5 straight; distance between apices of veins R1 and R2+3 longer than distance between apices of veins R2+3 and vein R4+5; distal part of vein R4+5 beyond vein M1 (hereafter distal vein R4+5) longer than cross-vein h (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="809FB014E91ECFB86EFEF01E18C517F8" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Intersection of vein R 1 with vein C (white), distance between apices of veins R 1 and R 2 + 3 and apices of veins R 2 + 3 and R 4 + 5 (blue), distal vein R 4 + 5 (pink) and setosity of proximal ventral half of vein C (red). A Romaleosyrphus bigoti sp. nov. B Sphecomyia weismani (Moran) C Criorhina bubulcus (Walker)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.55862.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/619714" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3</figureCitation>
); vein M2 absent; vein CuP+CuA short, curved; proximal ventral half of vein C with setae.
</paragraph>
